# Speech-to-Text Push-to-Talk Configuration
# This is the xbindkeys configuration file
# 
# Hold Ctrl+Alt+G to record, release to transcribe

# "~/bin/push-to-talk/speech-to-text-ptt start"
#   Control+Alt + g

# "~/bin/push-to-talk/speech-to-text-ptt stop"
#   Control+Alt + g + Release


# Alternative hotkey examples:
# ============================
# Uncomment one of these to use a different hotkey

# Option 1: Use Ctrl+Space instead
"~/bin/push-to-talk/speech-to-text-ptt start"
  Control + space

"~/bin/push-to-talk/speech-to-text-ptt stop"
  Control + space + Release

# Option 2: Use Super (Windows key) + V
# "~/bin/push-to-talk/speech-to-text-ptt start"
#   Mod4 + v
#
# "~/bin/push-to-talk/speech-to-text-ptt stop"
#   Mod4 + v + Release

# Option 3: Use Ctrl+Shift+Space
# "~/bin/push-to-talk/speech-to-text-ptt start"
#   Control+Shift + space
#
# "~/bin/push-to-talk/speech-to-text-ptt stop"
#   Control+Shift + space + Release


# Available modifiers:
# ====================
# Control  - Ctrl key
# Alt      - Alt key
# Shift    - Shift key
# Mod4     - Super/Windows key
# Mod1     - Alt key (alternative)

# Tips:
# =====
# 1. After editing this file, reload with:
#    ~/bin/push-to-talk/stt-start
#
# 2. To find key names, run:
#    xbindkeys --key
#    Then press the key you want to use
